<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="115" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,397,710]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,571,397,422]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">
Material and distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[499,566,397,422]" name="Cuba" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">Cuba</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
Observations on live animals, whole mounted afterward. One whole mount from Siboney (
<date box="[320,477,433,458]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" value="2017-04-04">April 4, 2017</date>
), on 
<taxonomicName box="[533,653,433,458]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Gracilaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[533,653,433,458]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">Gracilaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., 
<quantity box="[707,771,433,457]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" unit="m" value="0.3">0.3 m</quantity>
depth, salinity 34 ‰. Five whole mounts from Bueycabón (
<date box="[158,282,469,494]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">February 6</date>
&amp; 21, 2018), on leaves of 
<taxonomicName box="[576,814,469,494]" class="Insecta" family="Coleoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Thalassia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testudinum">
<emphasis box="[576,814,469,494]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">Thalassia testudinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[867,1119,469,494]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cymodoceaceae" genus="Syringodium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="filiformis">
<emphasis box="[867,1119,469,494]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">Syringodium filiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<quantity box="[1133,1196,469,494]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" unit="m" value="0.5">0.5 m</quantity>
depth, salinity 33 ‰. All reference material in HU (
<mcCollectionCode box="[488,539,505,530]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">VIII</mcCollectionCode>
.3.05– 
<mcCollectionCode box="[609,660,505,530]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">VIII</mcCollectionCode>
.3.10).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="115" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,397,710]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,541,566]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</emphasis>
The habitus and the internal organization of the studied specimen do not deviate from those mentioned in the original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus, E." box="[608,773,577,601]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" pagination="7 - 155" refId="ref11980" refString="Marcus, E. (1949) Turbellaria Brazileiros (7). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras, Universidade de S. Paulo, 14, 7 - 155." type="journal article" year="1949">Marcus (1949)</bibRefCitation>
and by 
<bibRefCitation author="Karling, T. G. &amp; Schockaert, E. R." box="[864,1193,577,602]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" pagination="5 - 19" refId="ref11817" refString="Karling, T. G. &amp; Schockaert, E. R. (1977) Anatomy and systematics of some Polycystididae (Turbellaria, Kalyptorhynchia) from the Pacific and S. Atlantic. Zoologica Scripta, 6, 5 - 19. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1977. tb 00755. x" type="journal article" year="1977">Karling &amp; Schockaert (1977)</bibRefCitation>
, including the typical blue pigmentation (
<figureCitation box="[371,462,613,638]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1567,1589]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,471,1549]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[172,1416,471,1549]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Paraustrorhynchus elixus (Marcus, 1954). A–B, male sclerotized structures (specimen from Cuba). Alcha evelinae Marcus, 1949. C, prostate stylet type III (specimen from Cuba). D, Habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2605864/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). The prostate stylet 
<typeStatus box="[699,747,614,638]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">type</typeStatus>
III (
<figureCitation box="[800,888,613,638]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1567,1589]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,471,1549]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[172,1416,471,1549]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Paraustrorhynchus elixus (Marcus, 1954). A–B, male sclerotized structures (specimen from Cuba). Alcha evelinae Marcus, 1949. C, prostate stylet type III (specimen from Cuba). D, Habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2605864/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
) of the Cuban specimens is 31–39 µm long (
<emphasis box="[1400,1420,614,637]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">x̄</emphasis>
= 35 µm; n = 6), which is within the range mentioned in literature: 33–53 µm (
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus, E." box="[1023,1176,650,674]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" pagination="7 - 155" refId="ref11980" refString="Marcus, E. (1949) Turbellaria Brazileiros (7). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras, Universidade de S. Paulo, 14, 7 - 155." type="journal article" year="1949">Marcus 1949</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Karling, T. G. &amp; Schockaert, E. R." pageId="8" pageNumber="115" pagination="5 - 19" refId="ref11817" refString="Karling, T. G. &amp; Schockaert, E. R. (1977) Anatomy and systematics of some Polycystididae (Turbellaria, Kalyptorhynchia) from the Pacific and S. Atlantic. Zoologica Scripta, 6, 5 - 19. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1977. tb 00755. x" type="journal article" year="1977">Karling &amp; Schockaert 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Jouk, P. E. H. &amp; De Vocht, A. J. - P." box="[221,481,685,710]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" pagination="145 - 157" refId="ref11630" refString="Jouk, P. E. H. &amp; De Vocht, A. J. - P. (1989) Kalyptorhynchia (Plathelminthes Rhabdocoela) from the Kenyan coast, with descriptions of four new species. Tropical Zoology, 2, 145 - 157. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03946975.1989.10539435" type="journal article" year="1989">Jouk &amp; De Vocht 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Artois, T. J. &amp; Tessens, B. S." box="[493,753,685,710]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref11031" refString="Artois, T. J. &amp; Tessens, B. S. (2008) Polycystididae (Rhabditophora: Rhabdocoela: Kalyptorhynchia) from the Indian Ocean, with the description of twelve species. Zootaxa, 1849, 1 - 27." type="journal article" year="2008">Artois &amp; Tessens 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
